            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "An MCD trade licence is a municipal permission to carry on a specified trade at a specified address, tied to the nature of the activity, while Shops and Establishment registration is a labour department registration covering working hours, leave and employee records. A Delhi eating house needs both; a small back office consultancy usually needs only the labour registration."
