            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "No GST is charged on an MCD trade licence fee, because a licence fee collected by a local authority in the course of a statutory function is outside the scope of GST under Notification 14/2017 Central Tax (Rate). The fee is booked gross as rates and taxes, and no input tax credit arises since no GST is paid."
          }
