<div class="gl-page">
  <section class="gl-hero"><div class="gl-wrap"><nav class="gl-crumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">&rsaquo;</span><a href="/glossary">Glossary</a><span class="sep">&rsaquo;</span><span class="cur">MCD Commercial Trade Licensing</span></nav><div class="gl-cat">Accounting Glossary &middot; City (local)</div><h1 class="gl-h1">MCD Commercial Trade Licensing: A Practical Guide</h1><div class="gl-byline"><span class="ok"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg></span><span class="who">Reviewed by CA &amp; CS Team, Patron Accounting LLP</span><span class="sep">&middot;</span><span>Last updated 22 Jul 2026</span><span class="sep">&middot;</span><span>6 min read</span><span class="sep">&middot;</span><span class="lvl">Advanced</span></div></div></section>
  <div class="gl-tocbar"><div class="gl-wrap gl-toc"><a href="#definition" class="gl-pill is-active">Definition</a><a href="#what-is" class="gl-pill">What it is</a><a href="#how-works" class="gl-pill">How it works</a><a href="#example" class="gl-pill">Example</a><a href="#mistakes" class="gl-pill">Mistakes</a><a href="#faq-section" class="gl-pill">FAQs</a></div></div>
  <div class="gl-body"><div class="gl-wrap"><div class="gl-grid"><div class="gl-main"><section id="definition" class="gl-sec"><div class="gl-eyebrow">MCD Commercial Trade Licensing: Definition</div><div class="definition-box"><p>MCD commercial trade licensing is the permission the unified Municipal Corporation of Delhi grants a business to run a trade the civic body regulates for public health or safety — a licence taken under the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act 1957. It sits in the books as a compliance cost, not a tax. It matters because a food, health or hazardous-goods establishment operating without the licence risks sealing, penalty and a break in its trade.</p></div></section><section id="what-is" class="gl-sec"><h2>What Is MCD Commercial Trade Licensing?</h2><p>A trade licence is a municipal permission — not an income-tax or GST registration — that lets a business carry on a specific activity from a specific address within a city. In Delhi the power to grant it comes from the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act 1957, chiefly its provisions on regulating dangerous and offensive trades and factories. Since the three erstwhile corporations were merged back into a single Municipal Corporation of Delhi by the DMC (Amendment) Act 2022 with effect from 22 May 2022, one unified MCD now issues these licences across the capital.</p><p>A Delhi business meets this when it opens or renews an eating house, sweet shop, clinic, gym or manufacturing unit — any trade touching food, health or public safety, the kind clustered in belts like Okhla and Nehru Place. Many low-risk trades have moved to a simple online registration, but Health Trade and Factory Licences remain live requirements for higher-risk categories, and the fee and renewal date must be tracked like any recurring compliance.</p><div class="key-terms"><p class="key-terms__title">Key terms</p><ul><li><a href="/glossary/ncr-inter-state-gst-reconciliation">NCR Inter-State GST Reconciliation</a> — Matching IGST and e-way bills across Delhi, Haryana and UP GSTINs.</li><li><a href="/glossary/delhi-nil-professional-tax-regime">Delhi Nil Professional Tax Regime</a> — Why Delhi payroll carries no professional-tax deduction.</li><li><a href="/glossary/gift-city-ifsc-tax-holiday">GIFT City IFSC Tax Holiday</a> — A location-based income-tax deduction in Gujarat&#x27;s IFSC.</li></ul></div></section><section id="who-applies" class="gl-sec"><h2>Who MCD Commercial Trade Licensing Applies To in Delhi</h2><p>The licensing regime reaches businesses across Delhi, most visibly the commercial and industrial pockets of Okhla and Nehru Place:</p><ul class="gloss-bullets"><li><strong>Eating houses and food traders</strong> — Restaurants, cafes, sweet shops and cloud kitchens in areas like Nehru Place need a Health Trade Licence alongside their FSSAI registration.</li><li><strong>Health and wellness establishments</strong> — Clinics, diagnostic labs, salons, spas and gyms fall in the health category that still requires an MCD licence.</li><li><strong>Manufacturing units in Okhla</strong> — Factories and workshops in the Okhla Industrial Area need a Factory Licence, and often a Health Trade Licence where the process is hazardous or handles inflammable goods.</li><li><strong>Low-risk offices and retail</strong> — IT offices and ordinary retail shops are largely exempt or need only a one-time online registration, not a full Health Trade Licence.</li></ul><p class="inline-links">See also: <a href="/accounting-services/delhi">Delhi city page</a></p></section><section id="how-works" class="gl-sec"><h2>How MCD Commercial Trade Licensing Works</h2><p>From opening a shop to holding a valid certificate, the process runs through set stages:</p><ol class="step-cards"><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">1</span><strong>Classify the trade</strong><p>The owner checks whether the activity is exempt, needs only online registration, or falls in a licensed category (food, health, hazardous) under the DMC Act 1957.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">2</span><strong>Apply online with documents</strong><p>Proof of premises, GST registration, ID and — for food — the FSSAI licence are attached, and the application and fee are submitted on the MCD portal for the zone.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">3</span><strong>Inspection or self-certification</strong><p>High-risk trades may face a site inspection; medium-risk trades get a self-certified registration certificate without pre-scrutiny.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">4</span><strong>Grant of the licence</strong><p>On approval the MCD issues the Health Trade or Factory Licence — the artefact that authorises the trade at that address.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">5</span><strong>Track and renew</strong><p>The licence carries a validity and renewal fee; the accountant diarises the renewal so the trade is never carried on with a lapsed certificate.</p></li></ol></section><section id="local-compliance" class="gl-sec"><h2>MCD Commercial Trade Licensing: Local Rules, Rates and Due Dates</h2><div class="gloss-table-wrap"><table class="gloss-table"><thead><tr><th>Requirement</th><th>Authority</th><th>Rate / due date</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Health Trade Licence (food/health/hazardous trades)</td><td>Municipal Corporation of Delhi, under DMC Act 1957</td><td>Fee varies by trade and area; valid for a fixed term and renewable on expiry</td></tr><tr><td>Factory Licence (manufacturing units, e.g. Okhla)</td><td>Municipal Corporation of Delhi</td><td>Required for factories; fee and renewal per MCD schedule</td></tr><tr><td>Low-risk trades</td><td>Municipal Corporation of Delhi</td><td>Many exempted or moved to one-time online registration / self-declaration</td></tr><tr><td>Shops &amp; establishment registration</td><td>Labour Dept, GNCTD (Delhi Shops and Establishments Act 1954)</td><td>File within 90 days of commencing work</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class="highlight-box"><p>Law stated as at 22 July 2026. Since the DMC (Amendment) Act 2022 (in force 22 May 2022) a single MCD issues these licences. Many low-risk trades are deregulated, but Health Trade and Factory Licences remain mandatory for food, health and hazardous categories — confirm the current category list on the MCD portal before assuming exemption.</p></div></section><section id="example" class="gl-sec"><h2>MCD Commercial Trade Licensing: A Practical Example (Delhi)</h2><div class="gloss-table-wrap"><table class="gloss-table"><thead><tr><th>Particulars</th><th>Amount (INR)</th><th>Treatment</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Health Trade Licence fee (restaurant)</td><td>12,000</td><td>Expensed as a licence cost for the term</td></tr><tr><td>FSSAI licence (separate requirement)</td><td>3,000</td><td>Booked separately — not an MCD levy</td></tr><tr><td>Professional consultant fee for filing</td><td>5,000</td><td>Charged to legal &amp; professional expenses</td></tr><tr><td>Total first-year licensing spend</td><td>20,000</td><td>Compliance cost of opening the outlet</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>A restaurant opening in Nehru Place, Delhi applies to the MCD for a Health Trade Licence and pays roughly ₹12,000 in licence fee for the term, plus a ₹3,000 FSSAI licence and a ₹5,000 consultant fee — about ₹20,000 of first-year licensing spend booked to legal and professional expenses. An IT office in the same building, by contrast, needs no Health Trade Licence, only a routine online registration — showing how sharply the requirement turns on the trade, not the address.</p></section><div class="gl-callout gl-callout--error"><span class="gl-callout__ic">!</span><div><div class="gl-callout__label">Common error</div><p>Assuming the licence was abolished: Treating every trade as exempt because low-risk categories were deregulated leaves a food or health business unlicensed → confirm the current category on the MCD portal before skipping it.</p></div></div><section id="mistakes" class="gl-sec"><h2>Common Mistakes With MCD Commercial Trade Licensing</h2><p>The licence is often mishandled where owners confuse it with other registrations:</p><ul class="gloss-bullets"><li><strong>Assuming the licence was abolished</strong> — Treating every trade as exempt because low-risk categories were deregulated leaves a food or health business unlicensed → confirm the current category on the MCD portal before skipping it.</li><li><strong>Confusing the Health Trade Licence with FSSAI</strong> — Taking only an FSSAI food licence and skipping the MCD licence leaves a municipal gap → obtain both, as they are issued by different authorities.</li><li><strong>Ignoring the Factory Licence in Okhla</strong> — Running a manufacturing unit on a shop-style registration understates compliance → apply for the Factory Licence where the premises is a factory.</li><li><strong>Letting the licence lapse</strong> — Missing the renewal date exposes the business to penalty and sealing → diarise the renewal like any statutory due date.</li></ul></section><section id="related" class="gl-sec"><h2>Related Accounting Terms</h2><p>City-compliance terms Delhi businesses meet alongside trade licensing:</p><ul class="related-terms"><li><a href="/glossary/ncr-inter-state-gst-reconciliation">NCR Inter-State GST Reconciliation</a> — Reconciling IGST and e-way bills across the NCR&#x27;s three states.</li><li><a href="/glossary/delhi-nil-professional-tax-regime">Delhi Nil Professional Tax Regime</a> — Why Delhi salaries carry no professional-tax line.</li><li><a href="/glossary/gift-city-ifsc-tax-holiday">GIFT City IFSC Tax Holiday</a> — A location-based income-tax deduction in Gujarat&#x27;s IFSC.</li><li><a href="/glossary">Accounting Terms Glossary</a> — Browse every accounting term in one place.</li></ul></section><div class="gl-callout gl-callout--summary"><span class="gl-callout__ic">&#10003;</span><div><div class="gl-callout__label">Quick summary</div><p>MCD commercial trade licensing is the permission the unified Municipal Corporation of Delhi grants a business to run a trade the civic body regulates for public health or safety — a licence taken under the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act 1957. It sits in the books as a compliance cost, not a tax. It matters because a food, health or hazardous-goods establishment operating without the licence risks sealing, penalty and a break in its trade.</p></div></div><section class="gl-cta"><div class="gl-cta__t"><h3>Need help with MCD Commercial Trade Licensing?</h3><p>MCD Commercial Trade Licensing sits inside your day-to-day books. Patron's CA-led team keeps them accurate, compliant and audit-ready.</p></div><div class="gl-cta__btns"><a class="gl-cta__primary" href="/accounting-services/delhi">Accounting Services in Delhi &rarr;</a><a class="gl-cta__phone" href="tel:+919459456700">Book a consultation: +91 94594 56700</a></div></section></div><aside class="gl-aside"><div class="gl-card gl-card--service"><div class="gl-card__eyebrow">Related service</div><div class="gl-card__name">Accounting Services in Delhi</div><p>CA-led bookkeeping, compliance and reporting for Indian businesses.</p><a class="gl-card__cta" href="/accounting-services/delhi">Explore the service &rarr;</a></div><div class="gl-card"><div class="gl-card__eyebrow">Related services</div><ul><li><a href="/accounting-services">Accounting &amp; Bookkeeping Services in India<span class="arw">&rarr;</span></a></li></ul></div><div class="gl-card"><div class="gl-card__eyebrow">Related terms</div><ul><li><a href="/glossary/ncr-inter-state-gst-reconciliation">NCR Inter-State GST Reconciliation<span class="arw">&rarr;</span></a></li><li><a href="/glossary/delhi-nil-professional-tax-regime">Delhi Nil Professional Tax Regime<span class="arw">&rarr;</span></a></li><li><a href="/glossary/gift-city-ifsc-tax-holiday">GIFT City IFSC Tax Holiday<span class="arw">&rarr;</span></a></li><li><a href="/glossary">Accounting Terms Glossary<span class="arw">&rarr;</span></a></li></ul></div></aside></div></div></div>
  <section id="faq-section" class="gl-faq-section"><div class="faq-expanded"><aside class="faq-expanded__aside"><h2 class="faq-expanded__title">MCD Commercial Trade Licensing FAQs</h2><p class="faq-expanded__lead">Common questions about MCD Commercial Trade Licensing for Indian businesses.</p><a class="faq-expanded__cta" href="/contact-us">Still have a question? Talk to a CA &rarr;</a><form class="faq-enquiry" action="https://www.patronaccounting.com/enquiry" method="post" novalidate><h3 class="faq-enquiry__title">Talk to a CA about your books</h3><p class="faq-enquiry__sub">Share your accounting software and we'll scope the work.</p><p class="faq-enquiry__context">Enquiring about: <strong>MCD Commercial Trade Licensing</strong></p><input class="faq-enquiry__input" type="text" name="name" placeholder="Your name" required><input class="faq-enquiry__input" type="email" name="email" placeholder="Email" required><div class="faq-enquiry__phone"><span class="faq-enquiry__cc">+91</span><input class="faq-enquiry__input faq-enquiry__input--phone" type="tel" name="phone" placeholder="Mobile" required></div><button class="faq-enquiry__btn" type="submit">Get a Callback</button><p class="faq-enquiry__msg" role="status" aria-live="polite"></p><div class="faq-enquiry__badges"><span class="faq-enquiry__badge"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg>CA-led team</span></div></form></aside><div class="faq-expanded__list"><div class="faq-expanded__item"><h3 class="faq-expanded__q" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="faq-a1">How is an MCD trade licence renewed?</h3><div class="faq-expanded__a" id="faq-a1"><p>An MCD trade licence is renewed online through the MCD portal before it expires, with the previous licence, property tax receipt, proof of premises and the renewal fee. Renewal is normally annual, and a lapsed licence attracts a late fee plus the risk of sealing of the premises. The renewal fee is booked as rates and taxes in the profit and loss account.</p></div></div><div class="faq-expanded__item"><h3 class="faq-expanded__q" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="faq-a2">What is the difference between an MCD trade licence and Delhi Shops and Establishment registration?</h3><div class="faq-expanded__a" id="faq-a2"><p>An MCD trade licence is a municipal permission to carry on a specified trade at a specified address, tied to the nature of the activity, while Shops and Establishment registration is a labour department registration covering working hours, leave and employee records. A Delhi eating house needs both; a small back office consultancy usually needs only the labour registration.</p></div></div><div class="faq-expanded__item"><h3 class="faq-expanded__q" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="faq-a3">Is GST charged on an MCD trade licence fee?</h3><div class="faq-expanded__a" id="faq-a3"><p>No GST is charged on an MCD trade licence fee, because a licence fee collected by a local authority in the course of a statutory function is outside the scope of GST under Notification 14/2017 Central Tax (Rate). The fee is booked gross as rates and taxes, and no input tax credit arises since no GST is paid.</p></div></div></div></div></section>
